      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROBERT JOHN (3) finished eighth last start over 1720m at Melton, beaten 18 metres, after a couple of good wins prior to that. Meets a similar line up and he can make amends. BAARLINEE (7) was restrained from a wide gate on the front line last start and couldn't come on, finishing 35 metres from the winner in eighth at Ballarat over 2200m. Perfectly placed and is sure to be there at the finish. JAKARTA NZ (9) didn't do a bad job when fifth over 1609m at Geelong last time out. Well worth an each-way chance. LADY SUSPICIOUS (4) missed the placings two runs back then did a great job to finish a neck back in second despite breaking in the run over 2190m at Mt Gambier a week-and-a-half ago. Beautifully placed and is sure to be thereabouts again.",
